## CACHING — REDIS ONLY, NO SIGNALR
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

IMPORTANT: There is NO SignalR in this project. Do not reference or import
Microsoft.AspNetCore.SignalR anywhere.

Cache strategy: Cache-aside with Redis. TTL = 30 seconds (configurable).
SDK polls every 30 seconds → changes reflect within one poll cycle.

Cache key pattern:
  "flagly:flags:{projectId}:{environmentApiKey}" → JSON of flag list
  "flagly:project:{projectSlug}" → project + environments metadata

IFlagCacheService interface (Flagly.Infrastructure/Caching/):
  Task<List<FeatureFlagDto>?> GetFlagsAsync(string cacheKey);
  Task SetFlagsAsync(string cacheKey, List<FeatureFlagDto> flags, TimeSpan ttl);
  Task InvalidateAsync(string cacheKey);
  Task InvalidateByProjectIdAsync(Guid projectId);

RedisFlagCacheService implements IFlagCacheService:
- Use StackExchange.Redis IConnectionMultiplexer
- Serialize with System.Text.Json
- On Redis failure: catch exception, log with Serilog, return null (fallback to DB)
- InvalidateByProjectIdAsync: use Redis SCAN to find all keys matching
  "flagly:flags:{projectId}:*" and delete them

When a flag toggle changes via web UI:
1. Save to DB
2. Call InvalidateByProjectIdAsync
3. Next SDK poll (within 30s) picks up fresh data from DB, re-caches

