## REST API ENDPOINTS (inside Flagly.Web/Controllers/ApiController.cs)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Auth: custom ApiKeyMiddleware reads header "X-Api-Key",
matches ProjectEnvironment.ApiKey, injects into HttpContext.Items["Environment"].
Unauthorized → 401 JSON response.

GET /api/client/features
  Header: X-Api-Key: {apiKey}
  Flow: check Redis cache → if miss, load from DB → cache with 30s TTL → return
  Response:
  {
    "environment": "production",
    "projectSlug": "my-project",
    "fetchedAt": "...",
    "flags": [{
      "name": "awesome-feature",
      "isEnabled": true,
      "description": "...",
      "type": "Release",
      "enabledForUserIds": ["u1"],
      "enabledForUserEmails": [],
      "userMatchMode": "UserId",
      "rolloutPercentage": 100
    }]
  }

POST /api/client/metrics
  Header: X-Api-Key: {apiKey}
  Body: { "flagName": "...", "wasEnabled": true, "userId": "u1" }
  Action: upsert FlagEvaluationMetric (5-min bucket), update flag.LastSeenAt

